# Clean-URL routing for the static marketing site (TASK-002 / REQ-002).
#
# Netlify-style `_redirects`: one rule per line, columns are
#   <from>  <to>  <status>
# Honoured natively by Netlify and Cloudflare Pages; see README ("Clean URLs")
# for the equivalent rules on netlify.toml / Vercel / nginx / Apache. This is
# URL mapping only and does NOT decide the host (REQ-033).

# Serve each page at its clean URL (200 = rewrite: content is served, the
# address bar stays clean). `/` is served from index.html automatically, so it
# needs no rewrite rule here.
/about-us      /about.html       200
/donate        /donate.html      200
/contact       /contact.html     200
/supporters    /supporters.html  200
/donate/thank-you  /thank-you.html   200
/donor-portal  /portal.html      200

# Canonicalise the raw .html paths onto the clean URL so each page has exactly
# one address. The `!` force flag is required because the .html files physically
# exist and would otherwise be served directly instead of redirecting.
/index.html       /             301!
/about.html       /about-us     301!
/donate.html      /donate       301!
/contact.html     /contact           301!
/supporters.html  /supporters        301!
/thank-you.html   /donate/thank-you  301!
/portal.html      /donor-portal      301!
